---

## 🔥 High Impact — Must Have

### 1. Student Notifications & Feedback View
**Problem:** Students submit essays but have no idea when they're graded. They must manually check `/submissions`.
**Solution:**
- Add a notification bell on the editor header
- Show unread grade count badge
- Toast notification when a new grade is received
- **API:** `GET /api/notifications` — fetch unread grades/feedback for student

### 2. Teacher Comments on Specific Text (Inline Annotations)
**Problem:** Teachers can only give a single overall `feedback` string per submission. No way to highlight a specific sentence and comment on it.
**Solution:**
- Add inline annotation support to the submission viewer on the dashboard
- Teacher clicks a passage → types a comment → saved as JSON annotations
- Student sees highlighted annotations when viewing their graded submission
- **DB:** Add `annotations jsonb DEFAULT '[]'` column to `grades` table

### 3. Due Date Reminders & Assignment Deadlines
**Problem:** Assignments have a `due_date` field but students see no countdown, reminders, or late-submission warnings.
**Solution:**
- Show countdown timers on the editor page when working on an assignment
- Color-code: green (>24h), yellow (<24h), red (overdue)
- Block or flag late submissions with a `late: true` marker
- Email/push notification 24h before deadline (future)

### 4. Assignment-Specific Submission Flow
**Problem:** Students currently type in the editor and submit with a free-text title. There's no structured flow tying a submission to a specific assignment.
**Solution:**
- Student dashboard page showing assigned work with status (Not Started / In Progress / Submitted / Graded)
- Click an assignment → opens editor pre-filled with assignment title, word limit shown
- Filter drafts by assignment

---

## ⭐ Medium Impact — Great Additions

### 5. Writing Progress Dashboard for Students
**Problem:** Students have no visibility into their own performance trends over time.
**Solution:**
- Student analytics page: avg WPM trend, integrity score history, grades received
- Show improvement charts ("Your WPM improved 20% this month")
- Gamification: streaks, badges for consistent writing

### 6. Rubric-Based Grading
**Problem:** Teachers grade with a single 0-100 score. No structured rubric criteria.
**Solution:**
- Allow teachers to attach rubrics to assignments (e.g., "Grammar: /25, Content: /25, Structure: /25, Originality: /25")
- Auto-sum rubric scores
- Students see breakdown per criterion

### 7. Real-time Collaboration / Teacher Preview
**Problem:** Teachers can't see student work until it's submitted.
**Solution:**
- "Live Preview" mode: teacher can view a student's current draft in read-only mode
- Optional — teacher can unlock this per assignment for supervision during exams
- Uses Supabase Realtime subscriptions

### 8. Revision History & Diff View
**Problem:** `replay_snapshots` captures writing history but there's no UI to compare revisions side-by-side.
**Solution:**
- "Revision History" tab on submission detail view
- Side-by-side diff showing added/removed text between snapshots
- Teachers can see exactly how the essay evolved

### 9. Bulk Actions on Dashboard
**Problem:** Teachers grading 73 submissions one-by-one is tedious.
**Solution:**
- Multi-select checkboxes on submissions
- Bulk grade (apply same score/feedback to selection)
- Bulk download as ZIP
- "Grade All as 100" for quick pass/fail workflows

### 10. Student Peer Review
**Problem:** No collaborative learning between students.
**Solution:**
- Teacher assigns peer reviews: Student A reviews Student B's essay
- Structured feedback form (not just free text)
- Anonymized or named reviews (teacher's choice)

---

## 🛠️ Quality of Life Improvements

### 11. Search & Filter Everywhere
- Dashboard: ✅ exists (search by student/assignment)
- Add: filter by date range, integrity score range, graded/ungraded toggle
- Student submissions: add search + filter by grade status

### 12. Keyboard Shortcuts
- `Ctrl+S` → save draft (currently auto-saves but no manual trigger)
- `Ctrl+Enter` → submit essay
- `Ctrl+Shift+E` → export as PDF
- Show shortcut hints on hover

### 13. Word Count Goal Indicator
**Problem:** Assignments have `max_word_count` but the editor doesn't show progress toward it.
**Solution:**
- Progress bar under the editor: "342 / 500 words"
- Color changes: grey → green → yellow (90%) → red (over limit)

### 14. Mobile-Responsive Editor
- Current editor is desktop-focused (1249 lines of complex layout)
- Add responsive breakpoints for tablet/phone
- Simplified toolbar on mobile

### 15. Email Integration
- Send grade notifications via email
- Send assignment reminders
- Use Supabase Edge Functions + Resend/SendGrid

### 16. Plagiarism Detection Enhancement
- Current: Jaccard similarity on 4-gram word shingles (basic)
- Add: comparison against a corpus of known essays
- Add: highlight the specific matching passages
- Add: external API integration (Turnitin-lite)

---

## 🏗️ Architecture Improvements

### 17. API Response Caching
- Cache profile lookups in memory (username → id is immutable)
- Use `Cache-Control` headers for static data (assignment lists)
- Reduces DB queries by ~40%

### 18. WebSocket for Real-time Updates
- Replace polling with Supabase Realtime for:
  - Dashboard auto-refreshes when new submissions come in
  - Student gets grade notification in real-time
  - Live typing indicators for exam proctoring

### 19. Error Boundary & Offline Mode
- Add React error boundaries around each page
- IndexedDB already stores drafts — enhance for full offline editor experience
- Queue submissions when offline, sync when reconnected

### 20. Role-Based Route Protection (Middleware)
- Currently each API route checks `session.role` individually
- Centralize this in Next.js middleware for cleaner code

---

## Recommended Priority Order

| Priority | Features | Effort |
|----------|----------|--------|
| **Sprint 1** | #3 Due date countdown, #13 Word count goal, #12 Keyboard shortcuts | Small |
| **Sprint 2** | #1 Student notifications, #4 Assignment submission flow | Medium |
| **Sprint 3** | #5 Student analytics, #9 Bulk actions, #11 Filters | Medium |
| **Sprint 4** | #2 Inline annotations, #6 Rubric grading | Large |
| **Sprint 5** | #8 Revision diff, #7 Live preview, #10 Peer review | Large |
| **Ongoing** | #17-20 Architecture improvements | Incremental |
